10:54.588 --> 10:57.756
We are going to get even
and catfish the catfisher.

10:57.758 --> 10:59.290
But I'm not being catfished.

10:59.292 --> 11:00.358
You'll see.

11:00.360 --> 11:02.327
We're gonna meet Kiersten
for a date

11:02.329 --> 11:04.996
and see what "she"
is really after.

11:04.998 --> 11:07.198
Any luck, you'll be abducted.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.100
♪♪

11:09.102 --> 11:13.338
<i>I realized the best way to
confront the enemy was head on.</i>

11:13.340 --> 11:14.305
Ooh!
Yes!

11:14.307 --> 11:17.976
<i>So I went to pick a fight.</i>

11:17.978 --> 11:20.045
Oh! Come on!
Dad!

11:20.047 --> 11:21.479
There's like two minutes to go
in the game!

11:21.481 --> 11:23.982
Sorry about that, bro.
We're not a big TV family.

11:23.984 --> 11:25.984
Since when?
There's one in every room.

11:25.986 --> 11:28.720
You put one in front of
your toilet like at a hotel.

11:28.722 --> 11:31.122
Nope.
Just not into screens.

11:31.124 --> 11:32.557
Hey, man, I understand.

11:32.559 --> 11:33.692
Mm-hmm.
[ Chuckles ]

11:33.694 --> 11:34.826
Kids, tell you what.

11:34.828 --> 11:36.728
Next time, you won't have to
watch it on TV.

11:36.730 --> 11:38.730
Got these clipper tickets
from one of my regulars.

11:38.732 --> 11:41.199
Oh, so you think you can just
take my kids to a clipper game?

11:41.201 --> 11:42.333
Man, I don't even know you.

11:42.335 --> 11:44.035
No, no, no.
There's six tickets.

11:44.037 --> 11:45.704
One for you, bow, and the kids.

11:45.706 --> 11:48.640
So you can just stay at home
alone with my mama at night?

11:48.642 --> 11:49.874
No thanks.

11:49.876 --> 11:51.309
Why are you hassling pop-pop,
dad?

11:51.311 --> 11:52.410
It's...

11:52.412 --> 11:53.978
"pop-pop"?

11:53.980 --> 11:56.481
Yeah. Because
he's twice as strong as pops.

11:56.483 --> 11:58.650
Well, I just started going
to crossfit.

11:58.652 --> 12:00.185
Got some extra passes, Dre,

12:00.187 --> 12:02.053
if you want to get in there
and, you know, mix it up.

12:02.055 --> 12:04.189
I am not for sale.

12:04.191 --> 12:06.424
But for the sake of my children,

12:06.426 --> 12:09.094
I will take
these clipper tickets.

12:09.096 --> 12:11.930
♪♪

12:11.932 --> 12:14.733
Hey, son.
Who's that?

12:14.735 --> 12:16.034
Some Manny that you hired

12:16.036 --> 12:18.269
to give your kids
a decent male role model?

12:18.271 --> 12:19.704
[ Chuckles ]
No.

12:19.706 --> 12:21.272
That's mama's new boyfriend.

12:21.274 --> 12:22.741
Say what? Him?

12:22.743 --> 12:24.342
Mm-hmm.
Wait a minute.

12:24.344 --> 12:26.344
What's he doing raising the roof
with my grandson?

12:26.346 --> 12:27.879
Because
he's twice as strong as you.

12:27.881 --> 12:30.415
That's why
the kids call him pop-pop.

12:30.417 --> 12:31.449
Say what?

12:31.451 --> 12:33.251
Davis is here to replace you.

12:33.253 --> 12:34.853
No, Davis got to go.

12:36.089 --> 12:38.590
Ohh, there he is.

12:38.592 --> 12:40.358
Why didn't I think of this
sooner?

12:40.360 --> 12:43.561
Who knows more about destroying
mom's happiness than you, pops?

12:43.563 --> 12:45.363
Well, she does bring out
the artist in me.

12:45.365 --> 12:47.298
So, what are you thinking, hm?
You gonna scare him?

12:47.300 --> 12:48.933
You gonna show him
where mama shot you?

12:48.935 --> 12:50.769
Cut his brake lines.

12:50.771 --> 12:52.871
Pillowcase-bat beating.

12:52.873 --> 12:54.539
It's not about
what I'm gonna do to him, son.

12:54.541 --> 12:55.907
It's about
what I'm gonna do to<i> her.</i>

12:55.909 --> 12:56.941
Ooh.

12:56.943 --> 12:58.643
I'm about to unleash the power

12:58.645 --> 13:01.112
[inhales deeply]
Of the south African Krugerrand.

13:01.114 --> 13:04.282
I suggest you take the family
to the movies tonight.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.451
To the movies?

13:06.453 --> 13:09.053
Oh, yeah.
A double feature.

13:10.457 --> 13:12.791
All set.

13:12.793 --> 13:15.760
"Kiersten"
will meet us tomorrow.

13:15.762 --> 13:17.428
Stop saying "Kiersten."

13:17.430 --> 13:18.963
It's going to be Kiersten.

13:18.965 --> 13:20.965
Sure.
You keep thinking that.

13:20.967 --> 13:23.768
Anyway, I told Kiersten
you'll both know each other

13:23.770 --> 13:25.270
because you're both
gonna be wearing...

13:25.272 --> 13:28.840
Now, get this...
White denim jackets.

13:28.842 --> 13:30.475
Like, what?!

13:30.477 --> 13:32.811
And then we'll post
the whole thing on YouTube

13:32.813 --> 13:35.113
so that the world can laugh
at the catfisher

13:35.115 --> 13:36.447
in a white denim jacket.

13:36.449 --> 13:38.950
You're wrong.
She's going to be there.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.618
We're soul mates.

13:40.620 --> 13:42.787
But in general...

13:42.789 --> 13:44.355
White denim.

13:44.357 --> 13:46.925
That's not something
I should be trying to pull off?

13:46.927 --> 13:49.994
♪♪

13:52.265 --> 13:56.434
Your son asked me to bring up
your plate, Quasimodo.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.269
What's up, baby girl?

13:58.271 --> 14:02.106
Just poured myself
two glasses of cutty sark.

14:02.108 --> 14:03.875
Would you care for one?

14:03.877 --> 14:06.110
Well, you know
I've never been one

14:06.112 --> 14:08.179
to let a cutty sark go to waste.

14:08.181 --> 14:10.381
Mm.

14:10.383 --> 14:13.384
[ R&B music plays ]

14:13.386 --> 14:14.953
Maybe we can dance a little bit.

14:14.955 --> 14:17.555
Your lasagna's getting cold,
Earl.

14:17.557 --> 14:19.991
Well, maybe I should
[Inhales deeply]

14:19.993 --> 14:22.227
Heat things up a bit.

14:22.229 --> 14:24.629
Okay, now.
Not the south African amulet.

14:24.631 --> 14:26.731
I thought you would've
pawned that by now.

14:26.733 --> 14:31.169
Waiting for gold prices to
get back to 2010 levels, baby.

14:31.171 --> 14:32.637
Earl, you don't fight fair.

14:32.639 --> 14:34.572
But I'm spoken for.

14:34.574 --> 14:37.542
And as much as the Krugerrand
gets me going,

14:37.544 --> 14:39.744
it's Davis that gets me there.

14:39.746 --> 14:40.879
Ugh!
[ Music stops ]

14:40.881 --> 14:42.347
Hey, Ruby, I was...

14:42.349 --> 14:44.249
Am I interrupting something?

14:44.251 --> 14:45.817
No. No, no, baby.

14:45.819 --> 14:48.052
Just a jackass in leggings

14:48.054 --> 14:53.124
that's too cheap to spring
for cutty sark golden jubilee.

14:54.327 --> 14:55.526
Come on, baby.

14:55.528 --> 14:58.196
♪♪

14:58.198 --> 15:01.599
<i>So, pops had failed.
I had failed.</i>

15:01.601 --> 15:04.769
<i>Maybe I could find an answer
in the fridge.</i>

15:04.771 --> 15:06.905
Ruby:
Mm, you're so bad, Davis.

15:06.907 --> 15:08.172
[ Giggles ] Yeah.

15:08.174 --> 15:10.008
<i>Unh-unh.
This was too much.</i>

15:10.010 --> 15:12.543
<i>I couldn't let it happen
in my own home.</i>

15:12.545 --> 15:14.679
<i>I knew what
my 10-year-old self would do.</i>

15:14.681 --> 15:16.114
Aah!

15:16.116 --> 15:18.683
[ Tumbling, shouting ]

15:18.685 --> 15:20.285
Not in my house.

15:20.287 --> 15:22.954
<i>But I knew
I would be tried as an adult.</i>

15:22.956 --> 15:24.355
<i>So this time around,</i>

15:24.357 --> 15:27.292
<i>I decided to do
the more mature thing.</i>

15:27.294 --> 15:29.928
Mama!
I'm having a heart attack!

15:29.930 --> 15:31.296
Oh, my god!
Oh, my god!

15:31.298 --> 15:32.931
Baby!
I got you, baby!

15:32.933 --> 15:34.465
Mama!
Call an ambulance!

15:34.467 --> 15:36.401
Oh, no, they'll never
get here fast enough!

15:36.403 --> 15:38.770
Get on my back!
I'll carry you to cedars!

15:38.772 --> 15:40.038
I'm not a doctor,

15:40.040 --> 15:41.306
but I don't think
he's having a heart attack.

15:41.308 --> 15:42.473
I<i> am</i> a doctor,

15:42.475 --> 15:44.375
and he's definitely<i> not</i>
having a heart attack.

15:44.377 --> 15:45.643
I see a white light!

15:45.645 --> 15:47.478
Oh, my god!
There's demons in the light!

15:47.480 --> 15:50.048
Stop! Stop! Dre, enough. Don't go!
Don't go into the light!

15:50.050 --> 15:52.216
I'm so sorry, Davis.
[ Dre and Ruby wailing ]

15:52.218 --> 15:53.551
You know what?

15:53.553 --> 15:55.286
I think this family's got
a few issues to work out,

15:55.288 --> 15:56.754
so I'm gonna...
I'm gonna leave you to them.

15:56.756 --> 15:57.922
Mm. Good night, Dre.

15:57.924 --> 15:58.823
Ruby, I'll call you.

15:58.825 --> 16:00.158
Oh, no, don't go, baby!

16:00.160 --> 16:01.492
Oh, mama!
I see the light again!

16:01.494 --> 16:02.827
Oh, no!
I see the light again!

16:02.829 --> 16:04.729
Devil, come out! Devil, come out!
[ Whimpering ]

16:04.731 --> 16:07.932
Okay.
I'm going back to sleep.

16:07.934 --> 16:10.568
<i>Was I proud of what I had done?</i>

16:10.570 --> 16:13.638
<i>Well, I got rid of Davis
and kept his clipper tickets.</i>

16:13.640 --> 16:15.373
<i>You tell me.</i>

16:18.611 --> 16:19.911
Got to hand it to you, son.

16:19.913 --> 16:21.646
That fake heart attack...
Inspired.

16:21.648 --> 16:23.948
The moment just came,
and I ran with it.

16:23.950 --> 16:25.116
Well, you did her a favor,

16:25.118 --> 16:26.417
'cause she looked ridiculous
with that young dude.

16:26.419 --> 16:27.418
Yes, she did.

16:27.420 --> 16:28.453
Earl.
Hm?

16:28.455 --> 16:29.454
We're gonna be late.

16:29.456 --> 16:30.621
Okay, baby.
Got to go.

16:30.623 --> 16:31.823
Hm?
Going to soulcycle.

16:31.825 --> 16:34.492
[ Laughs ]

16:34.494 --> 16:36.094
Good morning, Andre.

16:36.096 --> 16:37.028
Huh.

16:37.030 --> 16:38.763
And how are you feeling?

16:38.765 --> 16:40.598
Stronger.
Mm.

16:40.600 --> 16:42.467
Yeah, it turns out
it was only heartburn,

16:42.469 --> 16:44.869
but I really did think
I was having a heart attack.

16:44.871 --> 16:46.304
No, you did not.

16:46.306 --> 16:47.972
[ Chuckles ]

16:47.974 --> 16:50.274
But I understand
why you had to fake one.

16:50.276 --> 16:52.276
Ever since
you were a little boy,

16:52.278 --> 16:54.045
we've always been like this.

16:54.047 --> 16:55.313
Mm-hmm.

16:55.315 --> 16:57.281
You never wanted a man
to come between what we had.

16:57.283 --> 16:58.383
Mnh-mnh.

16:58.385 --> 17:00.852
Which is why,
out of respect for you,

17:00.854 --> 17:01.886
I snuck around.

17:01.888 --> 17:03.621
It's... you did?

17:03.623 --> 17:05.790
The gardener, the chimney sweep.

17:05.792 --> 17:07.191
Oh, baby, wake up.

17:07.193 --> 17:08.292
We didn't have a garden,

17:08.294 --> 17:09.961
and we sure didn't have
a chimney.

17:09.963 --> 17:11.329
[ Laughs ]
It did seem weird

17:11.331 --> 17:13.464
they had Christmas dinner
with us.

17:13.466 --> 17:15.500
But I thought,
now that you're 40,

17:15.502 --> 17:19.037
with four kids
and a wife, of sorts,

17:19.039 --> 17:21.472
that you might be able
to handle the idea

17:21.474 --> 17:23.574
of me being
in a real relationship.

17:23.576 --> 17:24.575
[ Chuckles ]

17:24.577 --> 17:26.044
I really should be.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.079
Yeah, and it's a shame
that you're not.

17:28.081 --> 17:31.149
But you know what?
Doesn't matter anyway.

17:31.151 --> 17:34.752
Davis and I are over.

17:34.754 --> 17:36.387
You are?
Yeah.

17:36.389 --> 17:37.588
It would've been fun

17:37.590 --> 17:40.024
to travel around the world
with my boyfriend

17:40.026 --> 17:42.894
and maybe see New Jersey.

17:42.896 --> 17:44.262
[ Chuckles ]

17:44.264 --> 17:46.931
I guess
I'll just buy a selfie stick

17:46.933 --> 17:50.001
and take the Amtrak
to Albuquerque.

17:50.003 --> 17:51.536
[ Scoffs ]

17:51.538 --> 17:52.870
Mm.

17:52.872 --> 17:56.074
♪♪

17:56.076 --> 17:57.241
Hm.

17:57.243 --> 17:58.342
Pops: Rainbow.
Huh?

17:58.344 --> 17:59.510
You got any shampoo?

17:59.512 --> 18:00.912
I got...
I-i-i got a situation.

18:00.914 --> 18:02.113
Oh, my god.
[ Laughs ]

18:02.115 --> 18:04.615
Look, I-i thought
I washed it out,

18:04.617 --> 18:06.918
but 10 minutes into soulcycle,
I started leaking oil.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.252
[ Laughing ]

18:08.254 --> 18:09.587
I'm... I'm sorry.

18:09.589 --> 18:12.023
I'm sorry.
I shouldn't be laughing.

18:12.025 --> 18:13.257
But hair dye?

18:13.259 --> 18:15.626
Really? Oh, my god.
Pops, you look ridiculous.

18:15.628 --> 18:17.595
I was trying to help my son.

18:17.597 --> 18:20.765
Oh, you were trying to help your son.
Mm-hmm.

18:20.767 --> 18:23.768
'Cause it seems like you went
to very great lengths

18:23.770 --> 18:26.003
to come between
Ruby and her man.

18:27.307 --> 18:28.606
Oh.
Too much.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.108
Yeah, I've been told that
before.

18:30.110 --> 18:31.442
Admit it, pops.

18:31.444 --> 18:34.745
You like your floozies,
but deep down,

18:34.747 --> 18:37.748
you want Ruby to wait for you.

18:37.750 --> 18:39.250
Oh, she waits for me.
Mm-hmm.

18:39.252 --> 18:40.952
In shadows
with a brick or a bat.

18:40.954 --> 18:42.787
One time a tube sock
full of batteries.

18:42.789 --> 18:44.655
You know why you're joking,
right?

18:44.657 --> 18:46.124
'Cause you know I'm right.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.558
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah.

18:47.560 --> 18:50.428
Ultimately, you know that
Ruby is the only one for you.

18:50.430 --> 18:52.730
I'm not saying you're wrong.
Mm-hmm.

18:52.732 --> 18:53.965
Just give me the shampoo

18:53.967 --> 18:56.334
so I can go take a shower
with my 25-year-old.

18:56.336 --> 18:57.768
Oh, that's disgusting.

18:57.770 --> 18:59.804
Oh, hey.
Hey, Davis.

18:59.806 --> 19:02.440
Dre, hey.
Uh, what are you doing here?

19:02.442 --> 19:04.942
I want to apologize to you
for last night.

19:04.944 --> 19:06.677
Nah, we're cool, man.
Nothing more to say about that.

19:06.679 --> 19:08.646
No, no. No, no, no, no, no.
There is more to say.

19:08.648 --> 19:11.782
Man, I almost pushed you
down the stairs.

19:11.784 --> 19:13.151
What's that?

19:13.153 --> 19:16.988
Look, you clearly
make my mother happy,

19:16.990 --> 19:20.091
and I just need to grow up
and let her be her own person.

19:20.093 --> 19:21.425
Hey, that's great, man.

19:21.427 --> 19:22.960
But I'm a little busy right now,
so if you could come back...

19:22.962 --> 19:24.162
Okay, not...
Ruby: Davis?

19:24.164 --> 19:25.930
Baby, if you find my drawers...
[ Gasps ]

19:25.932 --> 19:26.964
Ma?

19:26.966 --> 19:29.100
Oh. Andre.

19:29.102 --> 19:31.836
Uh, listen, th-this is not
what it looks like.

19:31.838 --> 19:33.638
Uh, there was a...
There was a hornet

19:33.640 --> 19:36.140
that came toward my drawers,
and then...

19:36.142 --> 19:38.543
Mama, this is exactly
what it looks like.

19:38.545 --> 19:42.046
And... and I'm okay
with that.

19:42.048 --> 19:44.315
Okay, I'm not really
okay with it,

19:44.317 --> 19:47.151
but if it makes you happy,
it's...

19:47.153 --> 19:49.153
Thank you, baby.

19:49.155 --> 19:50.955
I am happy.

19:50.957 --> 19:52.957
I'm very happy.

19:52.959 --> 19:54.325
[ Inhales deeply ]

19:54.327 --> 19:56.827
Very, very happy.

19:56.829 --> 19:59.297
[ Shuddering ]

19:59.299 --> 20:00.998
[ Whimpers ]

20:01.000 --> 20:03.067
♪ Oh, my lord! ♪

20:03.069 --> 20:04.535
♪ Lord, lord, lord! ♪

20:09.042 --> 20:11.042
Oh, white jacket.
Boom.

20:11.044 --> 20:12.710
Jack: She is a he.

20:12.712 --> 20:15.346
Diane: Who is definitely not
pulling off that white denim.

20:15.348 --> 20:17.315
Well, I'm going
to put an end to this.

20:17.317 --> 20:19.984
Yeah.
We're gonna want to film this.

20:19.986 --> 20:22.320
Yeah. Okay.

20:22.322 --> 20:23.821
Your attention, please.

20:23.823 --> 20:26.023
<i>This</i> man tried to catfish me.

20:26.025 --> 20:27.024
What?

20:27.026 --> 20:28.159
He was going to try to trick me

20:28.161 --> 20:30.661
into giving him money, an organ,

20:30.663 --> 20:32.597
and worst of all, my heart!

20:32.599 --> 20:35.166
Which is also
technically an organ,

20:35.168 --> 20:38.102
but in this case,
heart means affections.

20:38.104 --> 20:40.538
As you can see, I'm flummoxed.

20:40.540 --> 20:43.774
People of the coffee house,
boo this man!

20:43.776 --> 20:45.276
Dude, seriously?

20:45.278 --> 20:46.444
Booo!

20:46.446 --> 20:48.579
Why are you not booing?
Come on.

20:48.581 --> 20:50.248
Boo!
Junior?

20:51.751 --> 20:54.719
Kiersten?
You're real!

20:54.721 --> 20:57.388
See, Zoey?
I told you she was real!

20:57.390 --> 21:00.858
My selfie game is strong.
She came here for this.

21:00.860 --> 21:03.694
And this.
And all of this.

21:03.696 --> 21:04.729
[ Laughs ]

21:04.731 --> 21:06.097
Kiersten, tell 'em

21:06.099 --> 21:07.598
whose milkshake
brought you to the yard.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.934
[ Laughs ] Ah...

21:09.936 --> 21:12.136
Kiersten?

21:12.138 --> 21:14.338
Did we get all that?
Oh, yeah.
